title: For Sale/Trade:  Flagged?
postcontent: Have you been Flagged?Here are reasons the Mods will flag you....1 - Copyrighted Photo Violation, did you take a photo off the Factory or Distributor web site? or an auction site? it is not your photo, you cannot use it to sell your item.2 - wrong item in the wrong catagory, did you post a motorcycle in the shotgun for sale catagory?3 - multiple postings, same item listed in 2 or more cities...one location only....4 - Derogatory comments in your post - "if the item is still listed don't be stupid and ask if it is still for sale" - when your post is 2 weeks old should people assume it is still availible?5 - Scams - an UNREGISTERED account with little to no information is treated as a scam.6 - PRICE - if you list your item as FREE or with a price of "0" you will get flagged as a scam.7 - Bump Stocks - the Dealer that sold the LasVegas shooter a Bump Stock was sued for $100 Million and LOST.......take it to a gun show....8 - Remember, everything you post on the internet is there forever thanks to the "internet archives". Remember, Armslist was sued for people not playing by the rules....THINK before you post......Have a good day.

title: For Sale:  Very good condition Smith & Wesson 6906 9mm service quality all metal conceal carry pistol w/new 10rd  or used 12 rd magazine
postcontent: I have several of these (6906 stainless steel and 6904 blued version) fine generation three service quality conceal carry 9mm pistols, and can likely get a bunch more in the same good+ condition.  They are in very good shape, including the bores.   Might have been owned by Broward County Sheriff's Department, since they obviously weren't shot much.  All metal firearm. Totally reliable pistol. If you could figure out how to load their mags with beer cans, I bet  they would feed them with no problems  Super smooth and light trigger.   Very managable recoil. Traditional double and single action locked breech semi automatic pistol. Construction is steel barrel, slide assembly, internal parts, sights, trigger, hammer, levers, magazine body and innards, all built into a lightweight alloy frame. Only the grips, Mag safety plunger bushing, and magazine floorplate and follower are polymer. Barrel is 3 1/2 inch Devel type with ball joint muzzle collar that ensures accuracy and facilitates disassembly. Rifling is five groove right hand 1:18.75. Slide is serrated rear, .925 wide at the port; with ambidextrous safety levers that also decock the pistol. Slide also houses the firing pin and magazine safeties: the 6906 will not fire without magazine. Sights are matte blue steel dovetailed front and rear; dot front  These came from the factory with 12 round magazines.  My supplier didn't supply any magazines for them, but each will come with one brand new flush fitting 10 round magazine,  or a nice used 12 round flush fitting mag. 15 round mags are available for only $20, which seat well and are for the same 59 S&W series, but extend somewhat past the body of the pistol. I suggest getting it with the one flush fitting  mag, and getting the 15 round mag for $20 more. Its nice to have a 15 rounder for range time anyway.  I will not sell magazines separately without pistol purchase. While polymer frame pistols have their place  there is something to be said for a classic American made fully metal service quality pistol.  This baby eats Glocks for lunch.  This is the type of gun that you could pass on to your great grand kids after 5g rounds and it still will look and function great.   Super fantastic conceal carry pistol.  Smith & Wesson stands by its firearms, so buy with confidence.
